Sentencas: Residual thermal stresses in the electrolyte of the anode-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were estimated experimentally and numerically.
Titulo: Evaluation of the residual stress for anode-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction method was employed to measure the residual stress in the cell.
Titulo: Evaluation of the residual stress for anode-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: To estimate the residual stress precisely, a synchrotron radiation was used as the best means of X-ray source.
Titulo: Evaluation of the residual stress for anode-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The wavelength of the radiation beam used for the stress measurements was 0.154 nm, and the diffraction peak of YSZ (531) plane was used for the stress measurement.
Titulo: Evaluation of the residual stress for anode-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: The estimated residual stresses in the electrolyte were compressive stresses of around 650 MPa at room temperature.
Titulo: Evaluation of the residual stress for anode-supported SOFCs

Sentencas: Numerical calculation for the residual stress was also carried out.
Titulo: Evaluation of the residual stress for anode-supported SOFCs
